is electric field times
r, the dipole moment.

00:35:36.720 --> 00:35:40.420
What we have right now is A
dot p, the vector potential,

00:35:40.420 --> 00:35:43.149
times the momentum.

00:35:43.149 --> 00:35:44.690
So in other words,
I want to show you

00:35:44.690 --> 00:35:49.000
that the A dot p matrix element
is equivalent to an e dot r

00:35:49.000 --> 00:35:51.800
matrix element.

00:35:51.800 --> 00:35:54.150
This can be done with a
canonical transformation, which

00:35:54.150 --> 00:35:58.350
we'll do in A422, but here
let me sort of just show you

00:35:58.350 --> 00:36:01.220
the elementary discussion.

00:36:01.220 --> 00:36:03.780
We want to replace
the vector potential

00:36:03.780 --> 00:36:05.980
by the electric field.

00:36:05.980 --> 00:36:10.810
So therefore, we use the
fact that the electric field

00:36:10.810 --> 00:36:15.650
is the derivative of
the vector potential.

00:36:15.650 --> 00:36:18.280
And the derivative of
the vector potential

00:36:18.280 --> 00:36:23.920
means since we have an E the
minus i omega t dependence,

00:36:23.920 --> 00:36:28.210
that we simply multiply
with a factor of omega

00:36:28.210 --> 00:36:29.130
of the frequency.

00:36:32.220 --> 00:36:37.180
And what we obtain here
is then the amplitude

00:36:37.180 --> 00:36:40.710
of the electric field, E naught.

00:36:40.710 --> 00:36:45.260
So with that, we
have a matrix element

00:36:45.260 --> 00:36:49.945
which now involves
the electric field.

00:36:52.870 --> 00:36:57.635
But still the matrix element
of the momentum operator.

00:37:00.390 --> 00:37:04.210
But we can easily go from
the momentum operator

00:37:04.210 --> 00:37:08.080
to the position operator
by taking the fact

00:37:08.080 --> 00:37:10.040
that the momentum
operator is nothing

00:37:10.040 --> 00:37:17.110
else than the commutator of r
with the Hamiltonian H naught.

00:37:17.110 --> 00:37:20.370
The kinetic energy in
H naught is p square,

00:37:20.370 --> 00:37:26.500
and the commutator of r
with p square is simply p.

00:37:26.500 --> 00:37:30.475
So this is what I'm using here.

00:37:30.475 --> 00:37:34.858
And these are the p factors.

00:37:40.710 --> 00:37:48.140
So therefore if you take the
momentum operator between two

00:37:48.140 --> 00:37:59.400
states, we have this relation
between the momentum operator

00:37:59.400 --> 00:38:02.690
and the position operator.

00:38:02.690 --> 00:38:06.340
But we have not the
momentum operator.

00:38:06.340 --> 00:38:07.960
We have the commutator.

00:38:07.960 --> 00:38:11.910
And r H naught gives us r.

00:38:11.910 --> 00:38:17.090
But when H naught acts on the
a, it gives the energy in a.

00:38:17.090 --> 00:38:19.300
For the other part of
the commutator, which

00:38:19.300 --> 00:38:23.230
is H naught r, we can have H
naught act on the left hand

00:38:23.230 --> 00:38:28.644
side on b, and this
gives us the energy ab.

00:38:28.644 --> 00:38:32.460
For dividing by H
bar, what we get

00:38:32.460 --> 00:38:36.330
is the energy
difference, eb minus ea.

00:38:36.330 --> 00:38:39.950
Or in frequency units, omega ba.

00:38:39.950 --> 00:38:43.435
So this is now how we have
implemented the commutator.

00:38:46.460 --> 00:38:59.220
So that by inserting
this into this equation,

00:38:59.220 --> 00:39:04.890
we now finally obtain our
result for the matrix element

00:39:04.890 --> 00:39:08.210
in the dipole approximation.

00:39:08.210 --> 00:39:15.210
We have e, the electric field
amplitude, the polarization,

00:39:15.210 --> 00:39:22.890
the matrix element
b r a, omega ba,

00:39:22.890 --> 00:39:27.380
and here we have an 1 over
omega in the denominator, which

00:39:27.380 --> 00:39:31.451
came from the derivative of
the vector potential da dt.

00:39:47.470 --> 00:39:51.915
This here is the matrix
element of the dipole operator.

00:39:55.790 --> 00:40:01.610
So in other words, I
have derived for you

00:40:01.610 --> 00:40:04.862
that the interaction
matrix element

00:40:04.862 --> 00:40:15.420
in the dipole approximation
is the dipole operator

00:40:15.420 --> 00:40:21.720
times the electric field as
long as I make the approximation

00:40:21.720 --> 00:40:26.140
that this frequency factor's
on the order of [INAUDIBLE].

00:40:26.140 --> 00:40:32.530
Now this is clearly the
case in your resonance,

00:40:32.530 --> 00:40:35.240
so you should be safe.

00:40:38.840 --> 00:40:43.545
However, if you do the
more rigorous derivation

00:40:43.545 --> 00:40:48.770
of the dipole Hamiltonian
using canonical transformation,

00:40:48.770 --> 00:40:52.960
this factor of omega ba
over omega does not appear.

00:40:52.960 --> 00:40:55.096
So again, the dipole
approximations

00:40:55.096 --> 00:40:57.460
is better than I
presented today.

00:40:57.460 --> 00:41:02.070
The two approximations
topping the A squared term

00:41:02.070 --> 00:41:06.340
and approximating this
ratio of frequencies with 1

00:41:06.340 --> 00:41:10.619
is not necessary if you
use the other methods using

00:41:10.619 --> 00:41:11.660
canonical transformation.

00:41:23.130 --> 00:41:24.790
Any questions about that?

00:41:27.780 --> 00:41:29.190
Let me make one comment.

00:41:29.190 --> 00:41:31.510
I've shown you in
this derivation

00:41:31.510 --> 00:41:38.540
that the A dot p term,
the A dot p interaction

00:41:38.540 --> 00:41:43.180
within the dipole approximation
is identical to the e dot r

00:41:43.180 --> 00:41:44.770
interaction.

00:41:44.770 --> 00:41:49.190
So these are the same operators,
and if you would exactly

00:41:49.190 --> 00:41:52.170
calculate them in atomic
structure calculation,

00:41:52.170 --> 00:41:55.740
you would get the same coupling,
the same matrix element.

00:41:55.740 --> 00:41:59.330
However, in practice, there
are important differences.

00:41:59.330 --> 00:42:03.450
Because the E dot r
operator, the r operator,

00:42:03.450 --> 00:42:06.550
has a lot of weight
where the electron is

00:42:06.550 --> 00:42:10.100
far away from the nucleus
because it's multiplied with r.

00:42:10.100 --> 00:42:14.130
Whereas the p operator
emphasizes the derivative

00:42:14.130 --> 00:42:16.580
of the wave function,
and this is usually

00:42:16.580 --> 00:42:19.260
strong at close distances.

00:42:19.260 --> 00:42:22.840
So in the end, the results
have to be the same.

00:42:22.840 --> 00:42:25.670
But if you make an approximation
to your wave function,

00:42:25.670 --> 00:42:30.130
one formulation may be
numerically much more accurate

00:42:30.130 --> 00:42:32.040
than the other one.

00:42:32.040 --> 00:42:35.430
But fundamentally, the
two terms are the same

00:42:35.430 --> 00:42:39.988
and they are related the way
how I derived it for you.

00:42:39.988 --> 00:42:40.488
Yes?

00:42:40.488 --> 00:42:42.958
AUDIENCE: So when we say it's
the dipole approximation,

00:42:42.958 --> 00:42:46.190
does it mean that it's
a long wave length,

00:42:46.190 --> 00:42:49.310
or be the small field
or everything together.

00:42:49.310 --> 00:42:53.574
So what's the absolute
fundamental assumption of this?

00:42:53.574 --> 00:42:55.490
PROFESSOR: The absolute
fundamental assumption

00:42:55.490 --> 00:42:58.410
of the dipole
approximation is that we

00:42:58.410 --> 00:43:00.800
assume-- let me just scroll up.

00:43:06.170 --> 00:43:08.190
In the equation above,
we had an expression

00:43:08.190 --> 00:43:10.240
for the vector potential.

00:43:10.240 --> 00:43:18.570
And the dipole
approximation means

00:43:18.570 --> 00:43:21.270
that we can neglect the position
dependence of the vector

00:43:21.270 --> 00:43:25.160
potential A of r,
so we approximate A

00:43:25.160 --> 00:43:31.610
of r as being A evaluated
at the origin of the atom.

00:43:31.610 --> 00:43:35.540
And over the extent, over
the size of the atom,

00:43:35.540 --> 00:43:37.710
we do not have to consider
a spacial dependence

00:43:37.710 --> 00:43:40.380
of the vector potential.

00:43:40.380 --> 00:43:42.490
So this is sufficient.

00:43:42.490 --> 00:43:45.740
The other things that
e square is small

00:43:45.740 --> 00:43:49.760
and that we're
near resonance-- I

00:43:49.760 --> 00:43:51.480
have to make those
assumptions if I

00:43:51.480 --> 00:43:53.170
want to use this
elementary derivation.

00:43:53.170 --> 00:43:56.590
But with a canonical
transformation,

00:43:56.590 --> 00:43:59.790
as is discussed in
atom-photon interactions,

00:43:59.790 --> 00:44:03.190
you do not need those
additional assumptions.

00:44:03.190 --> 00:44:05.870
The only assumption behind
the dipole approximation

00:44:05.870 --> 00:44:10.750
is that one, and this means
that the extent of the atom

00:44:10.750 --> 00:44:13.092
is much smaller than the
optical wave lengths.

00:44:25.960 --> 00:44:26.510
OK.

00:44:26.510 --> 00:44:33.140
But there are situations where
the leading approximation

00:44:33.140 --> 00:44:34.050
vanishes.

00:44:34.050 --> 00:44:37.930
For instance, if two levels
have the same parity,

00:44:37.930 --> 00:44:41.820
then the dipole operator
between the two of them is 0.

00:44:41.820 --> 00:44:44.966
And then if you want to
have a transition between,

00:44:44.966 --> 00:44:47.340
or if you want to consider a
transition between those two

00:44:47.340 --> 00:44:52.410
levels, it will come
from next order terms.

00:44:52.410 --> 00:45:00.960
So let's now discuss higher
order radiation processes.

00:45:12.410 --> 00:45:15.190
So the motivation why I want to
discuss higher order radiation

00:45:15.190 --> 00:45:19.420
processes is because
in some basic courses,

00:45:19.420 --> 00:45:21.830
you only need the
dipole approximation.

00:45:21.830 --> 00:45:24.145
And you think the
dipole coupling

00:45:24.145 --> 00:45:26.630
is the only coupling
which exists in the world.

00:45:26.630 --> 00:45:28.447
And by going to
higher order, I want

00:45:28.447 --> 00:45:31.240
to show you that
this is not the case.

00:45:31.240 --> 00:45:35.050
Also I want to sort of
give you an idea what

00:45:35.050 --> 00:45:38.860
it means if you
have leading order

00:45:38.860 --> 00:45:40.310
transitions are forbidden.

00:45:40.310 --> 00:45:42.910
I want to sort of show
you how other terms come

00:45:42.910 --> 00:45:46.150
in which can couple two levels.

00:45:46.150 --> 00:45:53.600
And also, actually, when
you drive transitions

00:45:53.600 --> 00:45:56.950
within the hyper-fine structure
using radio frequency fields,

00:45:56.950 --> 00:45:59.780
you are not driving them
with the electric dipole

00:45:59.780 --> 00:46:00.546
approximation.

00:46:00.546 --> 00:46:03.110
You're driving them
with a magnetic dipole,

00:46:03.110 --> 00:46:07.820
and this is actually
the next approximation.

00:46:07.820 --> 00:46:09.610
So there's a number
of reasons why

00:46:09.610 --> 00:46:13.100
I want to show you what
the next order terms are,

00:46:13.100 --> 00:46:16.050
and how they actually
lead to beautiful result,

00:46:16.050 --> 00:46:19.222
magnetic dipole, and electric
quadrupole transitions.

00:46:35.090 --> 00:46:39.290
So our coupling term-- let
me just rewrite the equation.

00:46:46.450 --> 00:46:49.060
Let me now simplify the
notation by assuming

00:46:49.060 --> 00:46:52.075
that the polarization
is in the z direction

00:46:52.075 --> 00:46:54.135
and the propagation
is in the x direction.

00:46:56.910 --> 00:47:03.880
So then the coupling
had the dipole term.

00:47:03.880 --> 00:47:08.170
And the next order
term is ikx, and this

00:47:08.170 --> 00:47:10.150
is what we want to
investigate now.

00:47:16.670 --> 00:47:26.450
So the term kx or kr is smaller.

00:47:26.450 --> 00:47:28.626
And now I want to
show you explicitly

00:47:28.626 --> 00:47:31.380
that it's smaller by alpha.

00:47:31.380 --> 00:47:37.140
The k vector of the photon is
related to the frequency H bar

00:47:37.140 --> 00:47:40.650
omega divided by H bar z.

00:47:40.650 --> 00:47:44.126
If I approximate for
r, the relevant r

00:47:44.126 --> 00:47:46.910
when we indicate over
the wave function

00:47:46.910 --> 00:47:48.412
will be the Bohr radius.

00:48:00.860 --> 00:48:07.040
The relevant frequency, H bar
omega, well, it's a Rydberg.

00:48:07.040 --> 00:48:13.100
And the Rydberg is e square
over the Bohr radius.

00:48:13.100 --> 00:48:20.700
So now if I insert it, the
Bohr radius cancels out.

00:48:20.700 --> 00:48:23.770
And what we find is,
well, kr is dimensionless.

00:48:23.770 --> 00:48:27.130
We have to find something
which is dimensionless,

00:48:27.130 --> 00:48:30.620
but expressed by the fundamental
constants of atomic physics.

00:48:30.620 --> 00:48:34.287
And the only quantity which is
available for that-- it's not

00:48:34.287 --> 00:48:35.430
a surprise-- is alpha.

00:48:35.430 --> 00:48:37.960
The fine-structure constant.

00:48:37.960 --> 00:48:41.340
So therefore the
dipole approximation

00:48:41.340 --> 00:48:46.110
is actually the result of an
expansion of the plane wave

00:48:46.110 --> 00:48:50.185
e the ikr factor in
units of expansion

00:48:50.185 --> 00:48:51.536
in the fine-structure constant.

00:48:58.790 --> 00:49:00.180
OK.

00:49:00.180 --> 00:49:02.730
We want to look now
at the second term.

00:49:10.440 --> 00:49:14.050
And well, sometimes if
you deal with a term,

00:49:14.050 --> 00:49:16.800
we first make it
more complicated

00:49:16.800 --> 00:49:20.220
and then we simplify it.

00:49:20.220 --> 00:49:24.420
I want to sort of symmetrize
and anti-symmetrize it

00:49:24.420 --> 00:49:26.570
in the following way.

00:49:26.570 --> 00:49:30.150
This is p z x.

00:49:30.150 --> 00:49:35.890
So let me subtract z p x.

00:49:35.890 --> 00:49:39.000
But then, of course,
I have to add it.

00:49:45.940 --> 00:49:48.360
So now we have two terms.

00:49:48.360 --> 00:49:52.020
1 has a minus sign,
one has a plus sign.

00:49:52.020 --> 00:49:56.940
And as will see
in just a minute,

00:49:56.940 --> 00:49:59.690
is the first one is
magnetic dipole transition.

00:49:59.690 --> 00:50:01.780
The second one is electric
quadrupole transition.

00:50:04.550 --> 00:50:11.500
And we see that the first
one can be regarded as-- p

00:50:11.500 --> 00:50:14.890
z x is like p dot r.

00:50:14.890 --> 00:50:18.250
Its the y component of
the vector product and

00:50:18.250 --> 00:50:21.334
is therefore the y component of
the orbital angular momentum.

00:50:30.280 --> 00:50:32.760
OK.

00:50:32.760 --> 00:50:40.070
So let's focus for
now on this part.

00:50:40.070 --> 00:50:42.850
The second term, which is
the electric quadrupole term,

00:50:42.850 --> 00:50:44.255
we'll do in a few moments.

00:50:48.040 --> 00:50:54.600
The relevant matrix element
is now the matrix element

00:50:54.600 --> 00:50:58.130
of the orbital
angular momentum Ly.

00:51:11.770 --> 00:51:14.930
The p factor-- let
me just collect

00:51:14.930 --> 00:51:27.040
all of the constant imaginary
unit ehr AK over 2 mc.

00:51:27.040 --> 00:51:29.340
That looks complicated,
but it immediately

00:51:29.340 --> 00:51:36.855
simplifies when we realize that
this here is the Bohr magneton.

00:51:39.640 --> 00:51:44.132
And well, we still have
the vector potential.

00:51:44.132 --> 00:51:52.040
But the magnetic field is the
curl of the vector potential,

00:51:52.040 --> 00:51:55.120
and that means we will
assume that we have a vector

00:51:55.120 --> 00:51:59.270
potential propagating
in x, polarized in z.

00:51:59.270 --> 00:52:07.230
That means that our
magnetic field is that.

00:52:07.230 --> 00:52:13.650
So therefore ka, which
appears in our expression

00:52:13.650 --> 00:52:18.160
for the coupling, is
just the magnetic field.

00:52:18.160 --> 00:52:21.720
So therefore we find the
result that the next order

00:52:21.720 --> 00:52:23.940
term in the coupling
of the atoms

00:52:23.940 --> 00:52:27.432
to the electromagnetic
field have the simple form

00:52:27.432 --> 00:52:28.640
to the electromagnetic field.

00:52:28.640 --> 00:52:31.660
That it is the
magnetic field part

00:52:31.660 --> 00:52:38.240
of the electromagnetic wave
times the Bohr magneton

00:52:38.240 --> 00:52:47.480
times the matrix element, due
to the orbital angular momentum

00:52:47.480 --> 00:52:47.980
operator.

00:52:50.500 --> 00:52:55.510
And actually, if you take
the orbital angular momentum

00:52:55.510 --> 00:52:58.890
and multiply it with
the Bohr magneton,

00:52:58.890 --> 00:53:04.487
this is actually the operator
of the magnetic moment.

00:53:04.487 --> 00:53:06.820
Well, with a minus sign because
the electron is negative

00:53:06.820 --> 00:53:08.650
charged.

00:53:08.650 --> 00:53:11.750
Remember we had
introduced the operator

00:53:11.750 --> 00:53:12.750
for the magnetic moment.

00:53:12.750 --> 00:53:17.150
And the magnetic
moment was the g factor

00:53:17.150 --> 00:53:20.320
times the Bohr magneton times
the orbital angular momentum.

00:53:20.320 --> 00:53:24.320
And the g factor for
the orbital motion is 1.

00:53:27.270 --> 00:53:32.180
So therefore the interaction
we are talking about

00:53:32.180 --> 00:53:37.415
is the Bohr magneton
times the magnetic field.

00:53:40.540 --> 00:53:44.440
And, of course, what we
realize is the operator-- maybe

00:53:44.440 --> 00:53:48.230
I should back up for a second
and say what we actually

00:53:48.230 --> 00:53:51.625
realize is that
operator which couples

00:53:51.625 --> 00:53:59.640
to the electromagnetic field
has actually the form u dot b.

00:53:59.640 --> 00:54:04.070
This is exactly what we use
for the Zeeman effect in a DC

00:54:04.070 --> 00:54:05.570
magnetic field.

00:54:05.570 --> 00:54:09.720
But now the same
form u dot b appears

00:54:09.720 --> 00:54:12.414
for time dependent
magnetic field.

00:54:12.414 --> 00:54:13.830
And time depending
magnetic fields

00:54:13.830 --> 00:54:16.160
are not only creating
level shifts.

00:54:16.160 --> 00:54:20.160
They can also use transitions
through the matrix element.

00:54:20.160 --> 00:54:23.540
So in other words,
this whole exercise

00:54:23.540 --> 00:54:29.010
show you that the form u dot
b, which appeared naturally

00:54:29.010 --> 00:54:31.520
in the formulation
for DC magnetic field,

00:54:31.520 --> 00:54:34.046
also applies to AC
magnetic fields.

00:54:37.990 --> 00:54:41.040
But with that, I can
say, wait a moment.

00:54:41.040 --> 00:54:43.910
There are now two sources
for the magnetic movement

00:54:43.910 --> 00:54:45.270
of the atom.

00:54:45.270 --> 00:54:52.040
One is due to orbital
angular momentum,

00:54:52.040 --> 00:54:55.470
and the other one is due
to spin angular momentum.

00:54:55.470 --> 00:54:57.510
But the spin
angular momentum has

00:54:57.510 --> 00:54:58.995
a g factor, which is different.

00:55:01.730 --> 00:55:06.220
The approximation of the
[INAUDIBLE] creation is 2.

00:55:06.220 --> 00:55:10.050
So therefore I
mean, we will never

00:55:10.050 --> 00:55:13.000
get spin out of a
semi-classical discussion.

00:55:13.000 --> 00:55:16.945
Remember, we started with a
classical canonical treatment

00:55:16.945 --> 00:55:20.360
of the electromagnetic
field, canonical momentum.

00:55:20.360 --> 00:55:22.190
And now we are
running with it and we

00:55:22.190 --> 00:55:25.695
find that there is a coupling
between the magnetic field

00:55:25.695 --> 00:55:28.076
and the magnetic
moment of the atom.

00:55:28.076 --> 00:55:31.325
But, of course, we only get the
magnetic moment to the extent

00:55:31.325 --> 00:55:33.820
that it comes from
orbital motion.

00:55:33.820 --> 00:55:37.860
But in a semi-classical way,
I'm waving my hands now and say,

00:55:37.860 --> 00:55:39.600
well, what is valid
for the coupling

00:55:39.600 --> 00:55:43.300
to orbit to the magnetic moment
of the orbital angular momentum

00:55:43.300 --> 00:55:46.340
also applies to the speed.

00:55:46.340 --> 00:55:50.300
And I'm simply
adding the spin here.

00:55:50.300 --> 00:55:54.680
And with that, I've
derived for you

00:55:54.680 --> 00:55:58.810
the expression for the
interaction matrix element

00:55:58.810 --> 00:56:02.390
called M1.

00:56:02.390 --> 00:56:08.610
M1 is the magnetic
dipole transitions.

00:56:16.290 --> 00:56:17.860
Let me just write it down here.

00:56:17.860 --> 00:56:25.640
So this is nothing
else than u dot b.

00:56:35.440 --> 00:56:36.420
Any questions?

00:56:43.280 --> 00:56:44.500
Let me just summarize.

00:56:44.500 --> 00:56:46.580
You may find it
sort of interesting,

00:56:46.580 --> 00:56:50.450
when we discussed static
electric and static magnetic

00:56:50.450 --> 00:56:50.950
fields.

00:56:50.950 --> 00:56:52.900
For the static
electric field, we

00:56:52.900 --> 00:56:55.220
had an electric field
times the dipole.

00:56:55.220 --> 00:56:58.590
And we find this now as
a time independent term

00:56:58.590 --> 00:57:04.760
which can drive transitions
for interactions with time

00:57:04.760 --> 00:57:07.310
dependent electromagnetic
field, but we find it

00:57:07.310 --> 00:57:09.110
in the dipole approximation.

00:57:09.110 --> 00:57:12.980
The magnetic part,
u dot b, we find

00:57:12.980 --> 00:57:14.490
when we go to the next order.

00:57:14.490 --> 00:57:17.740
We find it as a
magnetic dipole term.

00:57:17.740 --> 00:57:20.940
But there are more
terms, and I just

00:57:20.940 --> 00:57:22.560
want you to illustrate
that and then

00:57:22.560 --> 00:57:25.320
I'll stop with that
multiple expansion.

00:57:25.320 --> 00:57:40.815
We had the second term,
the kr term, was this one.

00:57:40.815 --> 00:57:42.440
But then we sort of
anti-symmetrized it

00:57:42.440 --> 00:57:44.380
and symmetrized it.

00:57:44.380 --> 00:57:48.800
The first one here, we could
relate to orbital angular

00:57:48.800 --> 00:57:51.065
momentum and to the
magnetic moment.

00:57:51.065 --> 00:57:53.065
And now I would want to
discuss the second term.

00:57:56.530 --> 00:58:07.540
So that term uses a mixture
of position and momentum

00:58:07.540 --> 00:58:08.040
operators.

00:58:15.520 --> 00:58:22.860
But we know already how we can
get rid of momentum operators,

00:58:22.860 --> 00:58:28.076
namely by expressing momentum
operators as commutators

00:58:28.076 --> 00:58:28.950
with the Hamiltonian.

00:58:33.670 --> 00:58:43.820
So this gives us the commutator
of z with H naught times x

00:58:43.820 --> 00:58:50.380
plus z times the commutator
of x with H naught.

00:59:05.070 --> 00:59:05.570
OK.

00:59:05.570 --> 00:59:06.870
So we have two commutators.

00:59:06.870 --> 00:59:09.910
Each of them has two terms.

00:59:09.910 --> 00:59:12.260
That means a total
of four terms.

00:59:12.260 --> 00:59:13.720
And if you write
them down, you see

00:59:13.720 --> 00:59:16.690
that two are opposite
but equal and cancel.

00:59:16.690 --> 00:59:22.970
So therefore we are left
with two terms, which

00:59:22.970 --> 00:59:31.370
are minus H naught zx
plus zx times H naught.

00:59:36.660 --> 00:59:43.480
So this term has now the
following contribution

00:59:43.480 --> 00:59:55.890
to the coupling between
the levels A and B.

00:59:55.890 --> 00:59:59.850
So we have this
coupling matrix element.

01:00:08.455 --> 01:00:13.495
We have b factor mc Am.

01:00:19.360 --> 01:00:20.010
OK.

01:00:20.010 --> 01:00:26.065
So using the same approach
we used for the dipole matrix

01:00:26.065 --> 01:00:30.630
element, the H naught can act on
the state A on the right side,

01:00:30.630 --> 01:00:34.000
and can act on the state
B on the left hand side.

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:36.810
So this gives us simply
the energy difference.

01:00:40.540 --> 01:00:44.620
And what is left is
now a matrix element

01:00:44.620 --> 01:00:48.570
which only involves
position operators,

01:00:48.570 --> 01:00:49.980
but it uses a product of 2.

01:01:01.740 --> 01:01:07.320
And now, again, we express
the vector potential

01:01:07.320 --> 01:01:13.660
by the electric field,
as we had done before.

01:01:13.660 --> 01:01:27.270
And therefore we have now
expressed our coupling yes,

01:01:27.270 --> 01:01:29.620
by an electric field.

01:01:29.620 --> 01:01:33.430
And we assume that in the
near resonant approximation,

01:01:33.430 --> 01:01:35.520
as we had used for
the dipole coupling,

01:01:35.520 --> 01:01:37.195
that this is the
frequency omega.

01:01:44.390 --> 01:01:46.570
OK.

01:01:46.570 --> 01:01:50.440
So what we are
realizing is that we

01:01:50.440 --> 01:01:54.660
have one part of the
interaction Hamiltonian

01:01:54.660 --> 01:01:59.440
which couples levels
A and B, has--

01:01:59.440 --> 01:02:04.670
we call it E2, this
electric quadrupole

01:02:04.670 --> 01:02:11.945
because it involves elements
of the quadrupole tensor,

01:02:11.945 --> 01:02:18.262
or products of coordinates
x, y, y, z, x, z.

01:02:18.262 --> 01:02:21.870
And for this geometry, which
we assume with our plane wave,

01:02:21.870 --> 01:02:22.680
it is z, x.

01:02:26.026 --> 01:02:27.980
It couples to the
electric field.

01:02:32.830 --> 01:02:36.460
And this is the p factor.

01:02:36.460 --> 01:02:40.410
For a more general
geometry of plane waves

01:02:40.410 --> 01:02:43.740
with different polarization
going in different directions,

01:02:43.740 --> 01:02:51.570
we would have obtained different
products of coordinates.

01:02:51.570 --> 01:02:56.890
So let me indicate that, that
what we have picked out here

01:02:56.890 --> 01:03:00.290
is one specific component
of a tensor, which

01:03:00.290 --> 01:03:06.590
is sort of the tensor form
by using the position vector

01:03:06.590 --> 01:03:07.520
r twice.

01:03:11.710 --> 01:03:17.340
So in this derivation,
we found when

01:03:17.340 --> 01:03:19.730
we go beyond the
dipole approximation,

01:03:19.730 --> 01:03:26.202
when we take the kr term
in leading order, that we

01:03:26.202 --> 01:03:27.160
have two contributions.

01:03:30.580 --> 01:03:35.280
One is M1, magnetic dipole.

01:03:35.280 --> 01:03:37.761
The other one was
electric quadrupole.

01:03:42.820 --> 01:03:47.420
We realized-- I tried to
keep of all the p factors--

01:03:47.420 --> 01:03:57.840
that the electric quadrupole
matrix element is imaginary,

01:03:57.840 --> 01:04:01.350
whereas the magnetic
dipole was u dot b.

01:04:01.350 --> 01:04:02.850
There was no imaginary unit.

01:04:02.850 --> 01:04:03.350
It's real.

01:04:06.090 --> 01:04:13.620
That means that you will
never have any interference

01:04:13.620 --> 01:04:18.040
effect between magnetic dipole
and electric quadrupole.

01:04:18.040 --> 01:04:21.420
Or in other words,
when we have processes

01:04:21.420 --> 01:04:24.240
like spontaneous
emission where we

01:04:24.240 --> 01:04:26.670
take the square of
the matrix element,

01:04:26.670 --> 01:04:31.230
the square of the
matrix element will

01:04:31.230 --> 01:04:38.370
be the sum of the squares
of the matrix element

01:04:38.370 --> 01:04:41.766
for magnetic dipole and
electric quadrupole transitions.

01:04:51.700 --> 01:04:52.878
So let me summarize.

01:04:58.980 --> 01:05:05.630
We have discussed
three different ways

01:05:05.630 --> 01:05:12.100
how we can have coupling
matrix elements between two

01:05:12.100 --> 01:05:17.551
states, electric
dipole, magnetic dipole,

01:05:17.551 --> 01:05:24.140
electric quadrupole, E1, M1, E2.

01:05:30.355 --> 01:05:35.640
The operator was the
electric dipole operator.

01:05:38.300 --> 01:05:42.660
Here it was the operator of
the magnetic movement, which

01:05:42.660 --> 01:05:48.430
is orbital angular momentum
and spin angular momentum.

01:05:48.430 --> 01:05:53.430
And for the quadrupole, it
was the quadratic expression

01:05:53.430 --> 01:05:55.815
in the spatial coordinates.

01:05:59.220 --> 01:06:03.690
You can also ask
what is the parity?

01:06:03.690 --> 01:06:08.060
The electric dipole
operator connects

01:06:08.060 --> 01:06:13.090
states with opposite parity,
whereas both magnetic dipole

01:06:13.090 --> 01:06:15.900
and electric quadrupole
connect states

01:06:15.900 --> 01:06:17.828
even with the same parity.

01:06:23.620 --> 01:06:31.162
Magnetic dipole and electric
quadrupole transition

01:06:31.162 --> 01:06:34.310
are often called
forbidden transitions.

01:06:39.380 --> 01:06:41.520
Well, you would say it's
a misnomer because they

01:06:41.520 --> 01:06:44.790
are transitions, so they are
allowed, but they are weak.

01:06:44.790 --> 01:06:46.550
But this is the language we use.

01:06:46.550 --> 01:06:48.750
Weak transitions
are forbidden, which

01:06:48.750 --> 01:06:50.900
simply means they don't appear.

01:06:50.900 --> 01:06:52.520
They are forbidden
in leading order,

01:06:52.520 --> 01:06:55.124
but when you go to higher
order, they are allowed.

01:06:55.124 --> 01:06:57.540
You can, of course, say if
they were completely forbidden,

01:06:57.540 --> 01:06:59.520
there would be no
need to discuss them.

01:06:59.520 --> 01:07:01.800
But since they
are only forbidden

01:07:01.800 --> 01:07:04.035
at a certain level,
then, of course,

01:07:04.035 --> 01:07:05.410
it's interesting
to discuss them.

01:07:05.410 --> 01:07:07.310
And a lot of narrow
transitions which

01:07:07.310 --> 01:07:10.035
are relevant for atomic
clocks are highly forbidden

01:07:10.035 --> 01:07:10.535
transitions.

01:07:14.220 --> 01:07:18.490
The strength of them, which
usually scales with transitions

01:07:18.490 --> 01:07:21.270
with the square of
the matrix element,

01:07:21.270 --> 01:07:25.410
is on the order of 5
times 10 to the minus 5.

01:07:25.410 --> 01:07:28.570
So those transitions
are four or five orders

01:07:28.570 --> 01:07:38.400
of magnitude weaker Yeah than
an allowed E1 transition.

01:07:44.822 --> 01:07:46.798
So that's what they are.

01:07:57.166 --> 01:07:57.666
Questions?

01:08:06.064 --> 01:08:09.028
AUDIENCE: When people talk about
highly forbidden transitions,

01:08:09.028 --> 01:08:13.026
does this mean that's like
a optical transition, or how

01:08:13.026 --> 01:08:15.814
do we distinguish it from
just regularly forbidden?

01:08:17.351 --> 01:08:19.559
PROFESSOR: Actually I would
say forbidden transitions

01:08:19.559 --> 01:08:22.590
are weaker by alpha
to the power n.

01:08:22.590 --> 01:08:24.800
Here we have situations
where the matrix

01:08:24.800 --> 01:08:26.700
element is just
smaller by alpha.

01:08:26.700 --> 01:08:27.725
But, yes.

01:08:36.630 --> 01:08:38.474
Sometimes, yes.

01:08:41.300 --> 01:08:43.180
Some transitions are
highly forbidden.

01:08:43.180 --> 01:08:45.310
For instance-- I
try to remember--

01:08:45.310 --> 01:08:48.620
if you have hydrogen 1s and 2s.

01:08:48.620 --> 01:08:52.787
Because of s states--
actually, you

01:08:52.787 --> 01:08:55.120
are asking question about the
next chapter, namely about

01:08:55.120 --> 01:08:57.285
selection rules.

01:08:57.285 --> 01:08:59.029
Let me give it in words.

01:08:59.029 --> 01:09:01.779
The s, if you
connect two s states,

01:09:01.779 --> 01:09:04.076
they have both 0
angular momentum.

01:09:04.076 --> 01:09:04.770
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

01:09:04.770 --> 01:09:07.353
PROFESSOR: So you cannot have a
quadrupole operator connecting

01:09:07.353 --> 01:09:08.290
the two.

01:09:08.290 --> 01:09:12.060
It would violate
the triangle rule.

01:09:12.060 --> 01:09:14.840
You cannot have angular momentum
of 0 and angular momentum of 2

01:09:14.840 --> 01:09:16.840
and get angular momentum of 0.

01:09:16.840 --> 01:09:19.010
So therefore you
have a transition

01:09:19.010 --> 01:09:20.970
between two states
of the same parity.

01:09:20.970 --> 01:09:22.990
There is no dipole operator.

01:09:22.990 --> 01:09:24.410
There is no quadrupole operator.

01:09:24.410 --> 01:09:27.086
So you soon run into a situation
where it's highly forbidden.

01:09:31.750 --> 01:09:35.330
Sometimes you have the situation
that something is forbidden

01:09:35.330 --> 01:09:37.877
in non-relativistic
physics, but they're

01:09:37.877 --> 01:09:39.710
a relativistic term,
which makes it allowed.

01:09:43.116 --> 01:09:46.270
Well, there's also
that relativistic terms

01:09:46.270 --> 01:09:49.859
are fine-structure terms is
also an expansion alpha squared.

01:09:49.859 --> 01:09:52.149
So the symmetry may
allow it, but only

01:09:52.149 --> 01:09:54.730
in connection with
relativistic terms.

01:09:54.730 --> 01:09:56.610
I'm not an expert on
forbidden transitions,

01:09:56.610 --> 01:10:01.700
but usually you have transitions
which are multiply forbidden.

01:10:01.700 --> 01:10:03.860
They are forbidden
by spacial symmetry.

01:10:03.860 --> 01:10:05.640
For instance, in
the helium atom,

01:10:05.640 --> 01:10:09.640
singular triplet are
forbidden by spin symmetry.

01:10:09.640 --> 01:10:13.060
So if you have multiple
layers of being forbidden,

01:10:13.060 --> 01:10:15.400
then you get extremely
weak transitions.

01:10:15.400 --> 01:10:20.786
And one example, actually, are
the singular triplet transition

01:10:20.786 --> 01:10:25.260
in helium, or the 1s to
2s transition in hydrogen.

01:10:25.260 --> 01:10:27.650
They are not allowed
by simply going

01:10:27.650 --> 01:10:32.050
to the next order in
a multiple expansion.

01:10:32.050 --> 01:10:32.550
Yes?

01:10:32.550 --> 01:10:35.022
AUDIENCE: In ordinary
situations when

01:10:35.022 --> 01:10:37.827
you do have to possibly do at
least even more [INAUDIBLE]

01:10:37.827 --> 01:10:38.910
for the other transitions?

01:10:42.800 --> 01:10:44.930
PROFESSOR: I'm not
an expert on that.

01:10:44.930 --> 01:10:47.450
I'm not sure if there
is an atom which

01:10:47.450 --> 01:10:50.550
has a relevant transition which
is a [INAUDIBLE] transition.

01:10:50.550 --> 01:10:53.380
I've not heard about that.

01:10:53.380 --> 01:10:57.300
At least relevant examples
which are the fundamental atoms,

01:10:57.300 --> 01:10:58.600
helium and hydrogen.

01:10:58.600 --> 01:11:02.580
For hydrogen, at the
2s to 1 transition,

01:11:02.580 --> 01:11:05.060
the leading order
is the emission,

01:11:05.060 --> 01:11:08.670
the simultaneous
emission of two photons.

01:11:08.670 --> 01:11:10.730
So you have not
just one photon, you

01:11:10.730 --> 01:11:14.636
have two photons which,
of course, requires

01:11:14.636 --> 01:11:17.928
in the perturbation
expansion the immediate step.

01:11:17.928 --> 01:11:19.302
We discuss two
photon transitions

01:11:19.302 --> 01:11:20.960
at the end of this course.

01:11:20.960 --> 01:11:22.930
So in that case, it's
not in higher order

01:11:22.930 --> 01:11:26.010
in the single photon
multiple expansion,

01:11:26.010 --> 01:11:29.990
it becomes a
multi-photon transition.

01:11:29.990 --> 01:11:31.865
So this is one relevant case.

01:11:31.865 --> 01:11:37.580
And for helium,
triplet to singlet,

01:11:37.580 --> 01:11:39.385
this involves
relativistic physics.

01:11:42.258 --> 01:11:45.300
Actually, I mentioned it in
the other class on helium.

01:11:45.300 --> 01:11:47.739
I tried to look it up
and I want to show here,

01:11:47.739 --> 01:11:49.780
you have to go to this
order to get a transition.

01:11:49.780 --> 01:11:51.820
But when I tried to look
into the literature,

01:11:51.820 --> 01:11:53.650
I couldn't find a clear answer.

01:11:53.650 --> 01:11:56.420
Ultimately, it was
a relativistic term

01:11:56.420 --> 01:11:58.410
in the fully
relativistic formulation

01:11:58.410 --> 01:12:01.620
of the coupling of
electromagnetic fields

01:12:01.620 --> 01:12:04.880
to the atom.

01:12:04.880 --> 01:12:07.550
I'm not sure if you can put a
label on it and it would say,

01:12:07.550 --> 01:12:09.210
this is this and
this order term.

01:12:09.210 --> 01:12:11.510
It may actually
involve-- and we know

01:12:11.510 --> 01:12:13.600
that this happens in the
[INAUDIBLE] creation--

01:12:13.600 --> 01:12:18.020
that spin and spacial degrees
become treated together

01:12:18.020 --> 01:12:21.226
in the [INAUDIBLE] creation, and
maybe it's one of those terms.

01:12:24.031 --> 01:12:24.530
Yes?

01:12:24.530 --> 01:12:26.113
AUDIENCE: So what's
the actual meaning

01:12:26.113 --> 01:12:28.877
of interacting with
different Hamiltonians?

01:12:28.877 --> 01:12:32.947
Like, you wrote square root
of Hamiltonians and then--

01:12:32.947 --> 01:12:33.530
PROFESSOR: No.

01:12:33.530 --> 01:12:37.585
I meant actually the square
of the matrix element.

01:12:37.585 --> 01:12:38.126
AUDIENCE: Oh.

01:12:38.126 --> 01:12:38.625
Sorry.

01:12:38.625 --> 01:12:43.630
PROFESSOR: If you have,
for instance-- actually

01:12:43.630 --> 01:12:45.650
I will talk about it in
the next lecture when

01:12:45.650 --> 01:12:47.880
we discuss Fermi's golden rule.

01:12:47.880 --> 01:12:50.400
The transition strength
in Fermi's golden rule

01:12:50.400 --> 01:12:53.710
is proportionate to the
square of the matrix element.

01:12:53.710 --> 01:12:55.690
But now you would ask
the question, well,

01:12:55.690 --> 01:12:58.310
could we have some
interference between the two

01:12:58.310 --> 01:12:59.670
different processes?

01:12:59.670 --> 01:13:01.870
And I wanted to point
out at this level

01:13:01.870 --> 01:13:05.670
that we don't, because one
matrix element is imaginary,

01:13:05.670 --> 01:13:07.100
the other one is real.

01:13:07.100 --> 01:13:10.100
And if you take the complex
matrix element between two

01:13:10.100 --> 01:13:14.210
states and calculate
the square, the square

01:13:14.210 --> 01:13:17.950
of the complex matrix element
is the square of the real part

01:13:17.950 --> 01:13:19.680
plus the square of
the imaginary part,

01:13:19.680 --> 01:13:22.730
and there's no interference
trend between the two.

01:13:22.730 --> 01:13:26.410
So in other words, if you have
an atom which has a weak decay

01:13:26.410 --> 01:13:29.950
through M1 and a weak
decay through quadrupole,

01:13:29.950 --> 01:13:33.380
the two parts cannot
destructively interfere,

01:13:33.380 --> 01:13:35.575
because one is real,
one is imaginary.

01:13:35.575 --> 01:13:39.429
They add up in quadrature,
That's what I wanted to say.

01:13:43.410 --> 01:13:44.790
OK.

01:13:44.790 --> 01:13:49.040
So these were examples of
higher order transitions.

01:13:49.040 --> 01:13:55.420
And as the questions
have shown, this

01:13:55.420 --> 01:13:59.130
leads us to a discussion
of selection rules.

01:14:01.790 --> 01:14:06.510
Selection rules is nothing
else than a classification

01:14:06.510 --> 01:14:10.120
of possible transitions
according to symmetry.

01:14:10.120 --> 01:14:17.300
And it's a way of using well,
[INAUDIBLE] coefficients,

01:14:17.300 --> 01:14:20.650
angular momentum coupling,
or using, you would say,

01:14:20.650 --> 01:14:25.140
symmetry to figure out
if matrix elements are

01:14:25.140 --> 01:14:26.740
non-vanishing or vanishing.

01:14:26.740 --> 01:14:28.540
And I gave you
already one example,

01:14:28.540 --> 01:14:30.520
and I want to formalize it now.

01:14:30.520 --> 01:14:34.230
If you go between two s states
which have 0 angular momentum,

01:14:34.230 --> 01:14:37.400
you cannot have an operator
which is a quadrupole operator

01:14:37.400 --> 01:14:39.910
because-- and this is what
I want to tell you now--

01:14:39.910 --> 01:14:43.385
the quadrupole operator is a
spherical tensor with two units

01:14:43.385 --> 01:14:45.056
of angular momentum.

01:14:45.056 --> 01:14:47.730
And this would forbid
the triangle rule.

01:14:47.730 --> 01:14:52.440
This would forbid "conservation"
of angular momentum.

01:14:52.440 --> 01:14:55.080
So that's what I want to
discuss now in the next chapter,

01:14:55.080 --> 01:14:58.470
or at least get started
for the next five minutes

01:14:58.470 --> 01:15:02.110
by discussing selection rules.

01:15:02.110 --> 01:15:04.960
So the introduction
to selection rules

01:15:04.960 --> 01:15:08.750
is that we have
forbidden transitions.

01:15:08.750 --> 01:15:13.480
Forbidden transitions
are suppressed

01:15:13.480 --> 01:15:15.890
because we are forced
to go to higher order,

01:15:15.890 --> 01:15:18.710
and this is usually
higher order in alpha.

01:15:18.710 --> 01:15:23.680
So forbidden transitions are
weaker by some power of alpha.

